#: ../../../reference/config_files/editable_layout.rst:4
msgid "Editable layout files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/editable_layout.rst:6
msgid ""
"This file contain information consumed by :ref:`editable packages "
"<editable_packages>`. It is an *.ini* file listing the directories that "
"Conan should use for the packages that are opened in editable mode. Before "
"parsing this file Conan runs Jinja2 template engine with the ``settings``, "
"``options`` and ``reference`` objects, so you can add *any* logic to this "
"files:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/editable_layout.rst:11
msgid ""
"# Affects to all packages but cool/version@user/dev\n"
"[includedirs]\n"
"src/include\n"
"\n"
"# using placeholders from conan settings and options\n"
"[libdirs]\n"
"build/{{settings.build_type}}/{{settings.arch}}\n"
"\n"
"[bindirs]\n"
"{% if options.shared %}\n"
"build/{{settings.build_type}}/shared\n"
"{% else %}\n"
"build/{{settings.build_type}}/static\n"
"{% endif %}\n"
"\n"
"# Affects only to cool/version@user/dev\n"
"[cool/version@user/dev:includedirs]\n"
"src/core/include\n"
"src/cmp_a/include\n"
"\n"
"# The source_folder, build_folder are useful for workspaces\n"
"[source_folder]\n"
"src\n"
"\n"
"[build_folder]\n"
"build/{{settings.build_type}}/{{settings.arch}}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/editable_layout.rst:41
msgid ""
"The specific sections using a package reference will have higher priority "
"than the general ones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/editable_layout.rst:44
msgid ""
"This file can live in the conan cache, in the ``.conan/layouts`` folder, or "
"in a user folder, like inside the source repo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/editable_layout.rst:47
msgid ""
"If there exists a ``.conan/layouts/default`` layout file in the cache and no "
"layout file is specified in the :command:`conan editable add <path> "
"<reference>` command, that file will be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/editable_layout.rst:50
msgid ""
"The ``[source_folder]`` and ``[build_folder]`` are useful for workspaces. "
"For example, when using ``cmake`` workspace-generator, it will locate the "
"``CMakeLists.txt`` of each package in editable mode in the "
"``[source_folder]`` and it will use the ``[build_folder]`` as the base "
"folder for the build temporary files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/editable_layout.rst:54
msgid ""
"It is possible to define out-of-source builds for workspaces, using relative "
"paths and the ``reference`` argument. The following could be used to locate "
"the build artifacts of an editable package in a sibling ``build/<package-"
"name>`` folder:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/config_files/editable_layout.rst:57
msgid ""
"[build_folder]\n"
"../build/{{reference.name}}/{{settings.build_type}}\n"
"\n"
"[includedirs]\n"
"src\n"
"\n"
"[libdirs]\n"
"../build/{{reference.name}}/{{settings.build_type}}/lib"
msgstr ""

